cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT 

The paper deals with the analysis of intrusion detection records observed on the networks of several large, nonresidential organizations. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves time-series modeling and statistical analysis, which could be categorized under cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). The use of hidden Markov models and Markov Chain Monte Carlo techniques also suggests a possible categorization under cs.IT (information theory). Finally, the focus on network security incidents and the analysis of network risks and defensive efforts could be categorized under cs.NI (networking and internet architecture).
